{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> θῦμα</b>, ατος, τό, <br /> (θύω A) <b>victim, sacrifice</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 56.31 (Argos, 5th c.BC), 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1310, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 8, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 901, Wilcken “Chr.” 1 iii 3 (3rd c.BC), etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ θ. τοῦ Ἀπόλλωνος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 5.53 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; θ. θύειν, θύσασθαι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Politicus” 290e, “R.” 378a, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; usually of animals, but πάγκαρπα θ. <b>offerings</b> of all fruits, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 634 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; [ἁγνὰ] θ., opposed to ἱερεῖα, explained by Scholia as <b>cakes in the form of animals</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.126, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 782c, 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 1.26: proverbial, θ. Δελφόν\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] 'Barmecide's feast', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Iambi” 1.98. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <i>plural</i>, of <b>animals slaughtered</b> for food, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Gen.43.16. \">LXX</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, of persons, θ. λεύσιμον, probably of Clytemnestra, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1118 (Lyric poetry); πρόκεισθε θύματα τῆς ἡμετέρας ἐξουσίας 2nd c.AD: Herodianus Grammaticus 2.13.5. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>act of sacrifice</b>, ὧδ᾽ ἦν τὰ κείνης θ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 573. [θῠμα only “Supp.epigram” 2.518 (Rome, 4th c.AD), cf. Hdn.Gr.2.15.] \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumb